## Learn: Adding and Subtracting Polynomials

A polynomial is a monomial or the sum of two or more monomials.

* A binomial is the sum of two monomials
* A trinomial is the sum of three monomials
* The degree of a polynomial is the greatest degree of any term

Polynomials can be added or subtracted by performing the indicated operations and combining like terms.

* To subtract a polynomial, add its additive inverse
* The sum or difference of polynomials has the same variables and exponents as the original polynomials, but possibly different coefficients

A set is closed under an operation if performing that operation on any two elements of the set produces another element of the same set.

Because adding or subtracting polynomials results in a polynomial, the set of polynomials is closed under addition and subtraction.

### Study Tip

Constant terms have degree `0`, and variable terms with no exponent shown have degree `1`.

