## Learn: Multiplying Polynomials

Polynomials can be multiplied by using the Distributive Property to multiply each term in one polynomial by each term in the other.

* The product of polynomials is also a polynomial
* So the set of polynomials is closed under multiplication

To multiply two binomials, you can use the FOIL method.

### Key Concept: FOIL Method

Find the sum of the products of:

* First terms
* Outer terms
* Inner terms
* Last terms

Example:

`(2x + 4)(x - 3)`

`= (2x)(x) + (2x)(-3) + (4)(x) + (4)(-3)`

`= 2x^2 - 6x + 4x - 12`

`= 2x^2 - 2x - 12`

