## Example 4 — Simplify by Using the Distributive Property

Find:

`2x(4x^3 + 5x^2 - x - 7)`

Distribute `2x` to each term:

`= 2x(4x^3) + 2x(5x^2) + 2x(-x) + 2x(-7)`

`= 8x^4 + 10x^3 - 2x^2 - 14x`

