## Example 5 — Multiply Binomials

Find:

`(3a + 5)(a - 7)(4a + 1)`

### Step 1: Multiply two binomials

`(3a + 5)(a - 7)`

`= 3a(a) + 3a(-7) + 5(a) + 5(-7)`

`= 3a^2 - 21a + 5a - 35`

`= 3a^2 - 16a - 35`

### Step 2: Multiply the result by the remaining binomial

`(3a^2 - 16a - 35)(4a + 1)`

`= 3a^2(4a + 1) + (-16a)(4a + 1) + (-35)(4a + 1)`

`= 12a^3 + 3a^2 - 64a^2 - 16a - 140a - 35`

`= 12a^3 - 61a^2 - 156a - 35`

